<subSubSection pageId="130" pageNumber="131" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="130.[151,1436,1505,1820]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,294,1650,1676]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Ecology</emphasis>
. Mostly subtidal, rarely in the intertidal, known depth range: 
<quantity box="[1009,1099,1650,1676]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="0.0" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" unit="m" value="40.0" valueMax="80.0" valueMin="0.0">0–80 m</quantity>
; on mud, sand, and sand and shells substrates; no commensal association reported so far (
<bibRefCitation author="Haig, J." box="[826,948,1685,1711]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" pagination="1 - 440" refId="ref72816" refString="Haig, J. (1960) The Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Anomura) of the Eastern Pacific. Allan Hancock Pacific Expedition, 24, 1 - 440." type="journal article" year="1960">Haig 1960</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Gore, R. H. &amp; Abele, L. G." box="[960,1184,1685,1712]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" pagination="1 - 30" refId="ref72307" refString="Gore, R. H. &amp; Abele, L. G. (1976) Shallow water porcelain crabs from the Pacific coast of Panama and adjacent Caribbean waters (Crustacea: Anomura: Porcellanidae). Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 237, 1 - 30. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.237" type="journal article" year="1976">Gore &amp; Abele 1976</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="130" pageNumber="131" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="130.[151,1436,1505,1820]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1722,1748]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Glassell" authorityYear="1938" box="[321,551,1721,1747]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Porcellana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hancocki">
<emphasis box="[321,551,1721,1747]" italics="true" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Porcellana hancocki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to the western Atlantic 
<taxonomicName authority="A. Milne-Edwards, 1880" authorityName="A. Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1880" box="[1003,1432,1721,1748]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Porcellana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sigsbeiana">
<emphasis box="[1003,1149,1721,1747]" italics="true" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">P. sigsbeiana</emphasis>
A. 
<bibRefCitation author="Milne-Edwards, A." box="[1186,1432,1721,1748]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" pagination="1 - 68" refId="ref75003" refString="Milne-Edwards, A. (1880) Reports on the results of dredging, under the supervision of Alexander Agassiz, in the Gulf of Mexico, and in the Caribbean Sea, 1877, ' 78, ' 79, by the United States Coast Survey Steamer &quot; Blake, &quot; Lieut. - Commander C. D. Sigsbee, U. S. N., and Commander J. R. Bartlett, U. S. N., commanding. VIII. Etudes preliminaires sur les crustaces. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology at Harvard College, 8 (1), 1 - 68." type="journal article" year="1880">Milne-Edwards, 1880</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, differing from the latter by the much longer and slender P2–P4 (
<bibRefCitation author="Haig, J." box="[864,987,1757,1784]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" pagination="1 - 440" refId="ref72816" refString="Haig, J. (1960) The Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Anomura) of the Eastern Pacific. Allan Hancock Pacific Expedition, 24, 1 - 440." type="journal article" year="1960">Haig 1960</bibRefCitation>
). It is poorly known species, with only a few records (including one from 
<collectingCountry box="[521,612,1794,1820]" name="Panama" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Panama</collectingCountry>
) and no information on its life colour pattern.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
